      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${eps2025.toFixed(2)}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{opMargin2025}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash / (Debt)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate the intrinsic value of Marriott. We use the company's real cash generation to value the business rather than relative valuation multiples.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Marriott generated <strong>${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(1)} billion</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025. As an asset-light hospitality operator, Marriott produces strong cash flow without massive capital expenditure requirements.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}% per year</strong> for the next 5 years. This factors in the continued normalization of global travel and Marriott's ability to expand room count and RevPAR.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}% forever</strong>. This is roughly aligned with global nominal GDP growth, accounting for Marriott's scale and market leadership.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>Future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100)}%</strong>. With the 10-year Treasury at 4.18%, this represents a solid required rate of return for Marriott's business profile and debt levels.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF relies on a few core inputs. Here's our rationale for the three biggest levers.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Marriott operates an asset-light franchise model. They don't own most of their hotels, meaning they collect fees with high incremental margins. 8% growth accounts for modest RevPAR growth combined with steady net unit growth (new rooms added to the system).
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        The 10-year Treasury sits at 4.18%. Adding an equity risk premium for Marriott gives us a required return of 9%. This is slightly lower than a tech stock due to Marriott's mature, predictable fee stream, but still demands a solid return to justify equity risk.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        We assume 3% perpetual growth. Travel generally grows slightly faster than global GDP as the middle class expands worldwide, but given Marriott's already massive scale, 3% is a prudent terminal rate.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (Year 0)</td>
          <td>${fcf2025.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × {(1 + growthRateTerminal).toFixed(3)})</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ ({(discountRate * 100)}% − {(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%))</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
          <td>${netCash.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Equity Value</td>
          <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
          <td>{sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ MARGIN TRENDS ═══ -->
  <h3>Recent Margin Trends</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Metric</th>
          <th>Most Recent</th>
